text.section:
"Termination of service" includes:
retirement at the age of 70 years as required by Article IV, § 3 of the Maryland Constitution;
voluntary retirement;
resignation because of disability;
retirement by order of the Court of Appeals;
resignation;
nonelection or nonconfirmation when election or confirmation is required;
expiration of term without reappointment; or
abolition of the member's office.
